class Solution {
public:
    int hammingWeight(int n) {
        int count = 0;
        while (n) {
            count += n & 1;
            n >>= 1;
        }
        return count;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through each bit of the input number `n` using bitwise operations, counting the set bits. The `n & 1` operation checks the least significant bit, and `n >>= 1` shifts the bits to the right, effectively dividing `n` by 2. This approach is efficient and optimized for repeated calls.

